@startuml
title SensibLaw World-Model Metasystem 2026-04-04

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Monospace

rectangle "External Source Families" as SOURCES {
  component "Wikidata" as WIKIDATA
  component "AU" as AU
  component "GWB" as GWB
  component "Brexit" as BREXIT
  component "Future Sources" as FUTURE
}

rectangle "Lane Adapters" as LANES {
  component "Nat Lane" as NAT
  component "Assist / Reviewer Lane" as ASSIST
  component "Other Lane Adapters" as OTHER
}

rectangle "Shared World-Model Substrate" as SUBSTRATE {
  component "Cross-Domain Claim Model" as CLAIM
  component "Multi-Source Convergence" as CONVERGENCE
  component "Temporal Update Discipline" as TEMPORAL
  component "Contradiction Management" as CONFLICT
  component "Unified Action Policy" as POLICY
}

rectangle "Governed Outputs" as OUTPUTS {
  component "Review / Handoff Artifacts" as REVIEW
  component "Execution / Recommendation Gates" as GATES
  component "Audit / Provenance Trace" as AUDIT
}

WIKIDATA --> NAT
AU --> ASSIST
GWB --> ASSIST
BREXIT --> ASSIST
FUTURE --> OTHER

NAT --> CLAIM
ASSIST --> CLAIM
OTHER --> CLAIM

CLAIM --> CONVERGENCE
CONVERGENCE --> TEMPORAL
TEMPORAL --> CONFLICT
CONFLICT --> POLICY

POLICY --> REVIEW
POLICY --> GATES
POLICY --> AUDIT

note right of SUBSTRATE
One normalized process is now defined in code:
claim -> convergence -> temporal -> conflict -> policy
Lane rebinding is the next step.
end note

@enduml
